DC  Homoserine biosynthesis
DR  MetaCyc; HOMOSERSYN-PWY;
CC  Aspartate semialdehyde biosynthesis is a two step pathway. The product 
CC  of this pathway can be used in lysine biosynthesis, or in the pathway 
CC  leading to homoserine, which is involved in threonine, isoleucine and 
CC  methionine biosynthesis. There are three isozymes that differ in their 
CC  sensitivity to regulation by Lys, Met and Thr in Escherichia coli [1].
